title: Watch highlights: Portland Timbers get five goals from four players in rout of LA Galaxy
text:
The Portland Timbers did the unexpected in improbable fashion as they routed the LA Galaxy 5-2 in a road match Sunday.
The win boosted the Timbers into fourth place in Major League Soccer's Western Conference standings with one more game on their schedule, taking on the last-place Colorado Rapids at Providence Park this Sunday.
Portland trailed 1-0 at halftime. The Timbers came out in the second half dictating tempo and scored all five goals in a variety of ways. The Galaxy, who already clinched a spot in the postseason, managed to get within 3-2 before Portland shut out the defending MLS Cup champion the rest of the way for the win.
